# Changelog

## Unreleased

- Added depth-2 narrative API health end-to-end test coverage (frac-0094): `tests/test_narrative_api_health.py` now includes `NarrativeApiHealthEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `/health` HTTP surface through one cold healthy probe (auth-token-configured app, all checkers true, version `0.1.0`, world-store `list_events` probe call), one warm healthy probe (monotonic uptime, second probe call), one degraded probe (world store raises, ollama checker false, narrative engine importable), and a JSON-safe combined diagnostic round trip. `tests/test_test_narrative_api_health_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `cypherclaw.narrative_api.app` health behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4582 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

- Added depth-2 narrative API entity end-to-end test coverage (frac-0093): `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` now includes `NarrativeApiEntitiesEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing world-entity HTTP surface through Deniable character creation, multi-operation property mutation, get-by-ID round trip, Deniable-visible shared/entity listing, and JSON-safe diagnostic serialization. `tests/test_test_narrative_api_entities_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `cypherclaw.narrative_api` entity behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4580 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

- Added depth-2 musical-integration-runtime end-to-end test coverage (frac-0092): `tests/test_musical_integration_runtime.py` now includes `MusicalIntegrationRuntimeEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing musical runtime public surface through one room-mic scene: `senseweave.sample_dsp_activity.build_sample_dsp_activity(...)`, `sample_playback_engine.maybe_launch_event(...)` (with `STATE_PATH`, `OUTPUT_DIR`, and `launch_pw_play` patched for hermetic execution), the on-disk playback state, `self_listener.build_glyph_audio_state(...)`, `senseweave.sample_status.sample_status_text(...)`, and a JSON-safe combined `{activity, playback_state, glyph, face_text}` diagnostic round trip. `tests/test_test_musical_integration_runtime_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `sample_playback_engine`, `self_listener`, and senseweave sample helpers remain unchanged because they already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4578 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

- Added depth-2 music-theory end-to-end test coverage (frac-0091): `tests/test_music_theory.py` now includes `MusicTheoryEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_theory.py` public surface through C ionian scale lookup, ii-V-I chord parsing, smooth close voicing selection, key membership checks, note-name and frequency conversion, interval metadata, equal-tempered versus just fifth cents comparison, just-intonation chord generation, spectral partial generation, quarter-tone frequency conversion, and a JSON-safe diagnostic round trip. `tests/test_test_music_theory_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `music_theory.py` behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4576 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

